1 sell or lease to another person or entity in a manner that allows
2 the tenant or new owner to finish out the interior of the commercial
3 building, the county assessor shall establish the fair cash value of
4 such properties using the method prescribed by subsection B of this
5 section.
6 B. With respect to the commercial properties described by
7 subsection A of this section, the county assessor shall not
8 establish the fair cash value of the commercial building at a value
9 which is in excess of the direct cost of the materials used to
10 construct the commercial building prior to the installation or
11 furnishing of the interior of the commercial building.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective January 1, 2026.
